The '''Natural History Museum of Zimbabwe''' is located in [[Bulawayo]], [[Zimbabwe]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nomadtours.co.za/article_2006-4-27_7.html|title=Matobo National Park: History And Nature In Harmony|work=Nomad Tours|accessdate=25 October 2009|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723092104/http://www.nomadtours.co.za/article_2006-4-27_7.html|archivedate=23 July 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> on Leopold Takawira Avenue.<ref>{{cite map|title=Street Map of Bulawayo|publisher=Surveyor General of Zimbabwe}}</ref>

Officially opened in 1964, the museum contains exhibits illustrating the history, mineral wealth and wildlife of Zimbabwe, including the second largest mounted elephant in the world.<ref>{{cite web|title=City of Kings|url=http://www.met.gov.zw/places/byo.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061004065057/http://www.met.gov.zw/Places/byo.htm|dead-url=yes|archive-date=4 October 2006|publisher=Ministry of Environment and Tourism, Zimbabwe|accessdate=11 January 2010}}</ref>

